    <p>As opposed to the general liability policy outlined above, the errors and omissions policy provides coverage for liability arising from "wrongful acts." Wrongful acts are defined as any actual or alleged error, misstatement or misleading statement, or act of omission, neglect or break of duty of the insured, or any matter claimed against them solely by reason of their being or having been an insured during the policy period.</p>
    





